; Source: Computer Science Logo Style, Volume 2 Chapter 11,
; "Cryptographer's Helper".
; Source URL: https://people.eecs.berkeley.edu/~bh/v2ch11/crypto.html
; Modeled deterministic fixture: solve a small substitution-cipher sample with
; a canonical mapping inspired by the chapter's cryptogram discussion.

make "cipher [L B R A T Y]
make "clear [t o b e r n]

to decode.word :word
if emptyp :word [output "]
local [ch pos rest]
make "ch first :word
make "rest decode.word butfirst :word
if memberp :ch :cipher [make "pos which :ch :cipher output word item :pos :clear :rest]
output word :ch :rest
end

to decode.sentence :words
if emptyp :words [output []]
output fput decode.word first :words decode.sentence butfirst :words
end

print decode.word "YBL
print decode.sentence [LB RA BT YBL LB RA]
